w";s:4:"slug";s:31:"the-chair-netflix-series-review";s:5:"title";s:130:"Is Pewdiepie S Gaming Chair Just A Gimmick Clutchchairz Throttle Series Review In 2021 Small Game Rooms Small Kids Room Gamer Room";s:3:"alt";s:130:"is pewdiepie s gaming chair just a gimmick clutchchairz throttle series review in 2021 small game rooms small kids room gamer room";s:3:"url";s:71:"https://i.pinimg.com/736x/25/6b/1b/256b1be92713a49adc61a405079faaae.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQzW2xOZ2Q5NxVZAPjbaAQtkSrYQ6lGHAfzkA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:467;s:6:"height";i:700;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/786722628653791613/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:55:{i:0;s:71:"The Chair review Sandra Oh is first class in moreish university satire.";i:1;s:116:"Arriving like manna from heaven Oh is hilarious as the first head of the English department in Netflixs light fleet.";i:2;s:159:"As assembled the series possesses all kinds of classy trappings and intriguing themes as it blends comedy and drama without advancing to the head of the class.";i:3;s:86:"The Chair is funny as heck with some earned moments of real emotion and a killer cast.";i:4;s:82:"Six episodes flew by and we hope to see more of Pembrokes English department soon.";i:5;s:42:"The Chair Is Netflixs Best Drama in Years.";i:6;s:77:"The near-perfect show elegantly skewers the subject of free speech on campus.";i:7;s:121:"A review of The Chair the new Netflix series starring Sandra Oh Jay Duplass and Holland Taylor co-created by Amanda Peet.";i:8;s:46:"Netflixs satire of contemporary academia is a.";i:9;s:166:"Netflixs campus comedy The Chair starring Sandra Oh is elevated by a novel parenting crisis culturally specific workplace issues and irrepressible romantic chemistry.";i:10;s:269:"A whole new comedy drama series breaking new ground by focussing intimately on the lives of academics the Netflix comedy drama series titled The Chair stars the impeccable Sandra Oh as its protagonist and that is just the first of the many things the series gets right.";i:11;s:24:"The Chair Series Review.";i:12;s:88:"The Chair series showcases the ongoing in the department of English in Pembroke College.";i:13;s:110:"The department is not the best as it used to be and Sandra Ohs Ji-Yoon Kim is given the position to lead them.";i:14;s:133:"Sandra Ohs Ji-Yoon is put in an uncomfortable position throughout the series due to various situations and she shines through it all.";i:15;s:72:"So far reviews for Netflixs The Chair have been overwhelmingly positive.";i:16;s:72:"Its release timed as a new school year begins could not be more perfect.";i:17;s:94:"Season 1 of the series came out on August 20 and the internet has been buzzing about it since.";i:18;s:120:"The Chair acts as a window to the daily problems that female professors and teachers of color and different ethnicities.";i:19;s:138:"- Advertisement - The beauty of this series is how it deals with the most trivial conversations in the most humorous and satirical manner.";i:20;s:36:"The Chair is a riveting binge-watch.";i:21;s:105:"Over just six 30-minute episodes Peet deftly establishes a world rich in character comedy and compassion.";i:22;s:61:"The Chairs greatest strength is in where it eventually lands.";i:23;s:126:"With an accurate if heightened sometimes satirical portrayal of what its actually like to chair a department at least from my.";i:24;s:188:"If The Chair were just a collegiate-level romantic-comedy it would be a delight boosted further by its brevity but the shows eagerness to cover more ground is both exciting and a bit much.";i:25;s:193:"The Chair is a nice tidy six-episode binge and at about three hours total it feels like a slightly extended indie-film comedy set to a soundtrack of jangly college radio hits from the likes of.";i:26;s:189:"The series takes pains to show that the outcry isnt an overreaction by a few over-sensitive kids but a flashpoint within larger discussions about inclusivity sensitivity and social justice.";i:27;s:187:"One of the great strengths of The Chair Netflix is its vivid evocation of the requirements for survival in this place where a packed lecture hall and a youthful instructor count for more.";i:28;s:58:"Netflixs The Chair is a snappy binge for the long weekend.";i:29;s:123:"It might seem counterintuitive to recommend a workplace dramedy set in the world of higher education for Labor Day weekend.";i:30;s:82:"Its wise to accept that The Chair is closer to truth and further away from comedy.";i:31;s:69:"This review of Netflixs The Chair season 1 does not contain spoilers.";i:32;s:39:"Read the ending explained for season 1.";i:33;s:83:"There are so many ways you can look at The Chair as it tackles more than one story.";i:34;s:49:"The core story is about the first woman of color.";i:35;s:15:"August 26 2021.";i:36;s:19:"475 4 minutes read.";i:37;s:138:"The Chair a new six-episode Netflix series about a fictional liberal arts university touches on all the main hot-button issues of the day.";i:38;s:51:"Overall there is much to appreciate about the show.";i:39;s:35:"The Chair 2021 TV series The Chair.";i:40;s:81:"2021 TV series The Chair is an American comedy-drama streaming television series.";i:41;s:53:"The series was released on Netflix on August 20 2021.";i:42;s:78:"It is set at the fictional Pembroke University in what seems like New England.";i:43;s:69:"The Chair is a NEW Netflix series starring Sandra Oh and Jay Dupalss.";i:44;s:52:"This is my official The Chair Netflix series review.";i:45;s:35:"Share your The Chair review and re.";i:46;s:122:"In addition to Ohs charms Chair is a darkly funny satire skewering aspects of modern higher education with veritable glee.";i:47;s:117:"The characters are sharply written and feel real and grounded even as the events surrounding them become more crazed.";i:48;s:62:"Netflixs The Chair Is a Gentle Farce That Wants for More Bite.";i:49;s:41:"The Best Horror Movies on Hulu Right Now.";i:50;s:108:"The series might have made its points more effectively had it leaned into this comical aspect a little more.";i:51;s:103:"In one late scene Ji-Yoon sits in a therapists office relaying her various personal problems in detail.";i:52;s:178:"In the latest of Netflixs forays into television writers Amanda Peet and Annie Julia Wyman who completed her PhD in English at Harvard in 2017 crafted The Chair a new miniseries.";i:53;s:76:"There is a poignant pleasure to be found in loving something past its prime.";i:54;s:117:"Watching The Chair a Netflix limited series in which Sandra Oh plays an academic struggling to stave off the decline.";}}